# ============================================================================
#  Helgrind suppressions for Codexion
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Known FALSE POSITIVE with glibc >= 2.34 condition variables.
#
#  glibc's pthread_cond_timedwait internally performs a futex/signal step
#  ("__condvar_quiesce_and_switch_g1") while the waiter has atomically
#  released its mutex. Helgrind intercepts that INTERNAL signal and reports:
#      "pthread_cond_{signal,broadcast}: associated lock is not held by
#       calling thread"
#  even though our code calls pthread_cond_timedwait with the mutex held,
#  exactly as required.
#
#  Evidence it is not our bug:
#    - ThreadSanitizer reports 0 warnings on the same run.
#    - Helgrind reports 0 errors at low thread counts.
#    - The flagged signal frame is inside glibc (pthread_cond_wait.c),
#      not at any of our pthread_cond_broadcast call sites.
#
#  Usage:
#    valgrind --tool=helgrind --suppressions=helgrind.supp ./codexion ...
# ============================================================================

{
   glibc-condvar-timedwait-internal-signal
   Helgrind:Misc
   fun:pthread_cond_signal_WRK
   fun:__pthread_cond_wait_common
   ...
}
